<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 Roszkowski, Mieczyslaw/10:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-16">August 16,
                                1940</date>.<lb/>[Received August 17—1:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1030. Department’s 192, March 30th, and Embassy’s 586, May 27th.<note n="99" xml:id="d886fn99">Neither printed.</note> Embassy now
                            informed Roszkowski arrested June 29th for alleged illegal possession
                            firearms and was to be tried July 22nd but trial postponed. Inquiry in
                            matter being addressed to Foreign Office.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>